org.missile.model
Class GameEngine

java.lang.Object
  org.missile.model.GameEngine
All Implemented Interfaces:
GameElementObserver
public class GameEngine
extends java.lang.Object
implements GameElementObserver

Model of the application.

Contains the logic of the system and know how the business models are related and how to them.

This class acts as a facade for the Logic of the application. The reason behind this is the use of the Facade Design Pattern.

Author:
Luis Carlos Mateos

shootEnemyMissile

public void shootEnemyMissile(int x0,
                              int y0,
                              int x1,
                              int y1,
                              double shootingFactor,
                              double missileSpeed)
Shoots an enemy missile with an uncertain probability.

Parameters:
x0 - origin x axis coordinate
y0 - origin y axis coordinate
x1 - destination x axis coordinate
y1 - destination y axis coordinate
shootingFactor - defines how easy for the enemy is to shoot a missile against us. the lower this value is, the harder the game will become. A good value is 99.5
missileSpeed - defines how fast a enemy missile will travel. The faster they travel, the harder the game is.
